                    <abstract lang="eng">In this paper we present a novel approach to model perceptual grouping based on phase and frequency synchronization in a network of coupled Kuramoto oscillators. Transferring the grouping concept from the Competitive Layer Model (CLM) to a network of Kuramoto oscillators, we preserve the excellent grouping capabilities of the CLM, while dramatically improving the convergence rate, robustness to noise, and computational performance, which is verified in a series of artificial grouping experiments.</abstract>
